President Obama met with his counterterrorism and homeland security team to discuss efforts following the Brussels terrorist attacks. They briefed him that there is currently no specific, credible intelligence of any plot to conduct similar attacks in the United States. The President was updated on expanded information-sharing with international partners and efforts to disrupt and counter external plots from ISIL-controlled territory. He also received briefings on addressing ISIL's use of the Internet to recruit and incite violence. The President directed his team to intensify efforts to degrade and destroy ISIL and ensure the United States is disrupting any external plotting efforts.